      <p style="color:#4B5563;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px;">
        A Genuineness Certificate is a legal document issued by a controlling authority that validates the information and qualifications within a document and certifies its legitimacy. It serves as strong proof of authenticity for a wide range of personal, academic, and professional records.
      </p>
      <p style="color:#4B5563;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px;">
        In the UAE, this certificate is often required by government bodies, professional associations, and academic institutions as part of employment, licensing, or official application processes.
      </p>
      <div style="background:#F0FFFE;border:1px solid #B2F5EA;border-radius:12px;padding:18px;">
        <h3 style="color:#1A202C;font-size:0.95rem;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 6px;">Issued by a Controlling Authority</h3>
        <p style="color:#4B5563;font-size:0.85rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">
          The certificate is issued after thorough verification of the submitted documents by the relevant controlling authority. It covers facts relating to birth, marital status, death, health, academic credentials, and professional capacity.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <div style="position:relative;border-radius:20px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1589829545856-d10d557cf95f?w=800&q=80" alt="Genuineness Certificate UAE" style="width:100%;height:440px;object-fit:cover;display:block;" />
        <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:linear-gradient(180deg,transparent 50%,rgba(26,32,44,0.72) 100%);"></div>
        <div style="position:absolute;bottom:20px;left:20px;right:20px;">
